# Deploy to GitHub

When the user asks to deploy, push, or publish code to GitHub, use this workflow.

## Repository

- **URL**: https://github.com/soodongpark-product/Vibe-Coding.git
- **Branch**: main
- **Project root**: `c:\Users\soodo\Cursor Projects`

## Git Path

Git may not be in PATH. Use the full path:
```
C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe
```

## Deployment Commands

1. **Stage changes**
   ```powershell
   cd "c:\Users\soodo\Cursor Projects"; & "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe" add .
   ```

2. **Commit** (use a descriptive message)
   ```powershell
   & "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe" commit -m "Your commit message"
   ```

3. **Push**
   ```powershell
   & "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe" push origin main
   ```

## One-liner for quick deploy

```powershell
cd "c:\Users\soodo\Cursor Projects"; & "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe" add .; & "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe" commit -m "Update: describe changes"; & "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe" push origin main
```

## Notes

- Remote `origin` is already configured for this repo
- If commit fails with "Author identity unknown", set locally:
  ```
  git config user.email "soodongpark-product@users.noreply.github.com"
  git config user.name "soodongpark-product"
  ```
